Package: omicsuite
Title: Portfolio-Grade Pipelines for Survival, RNA-Seq, Epidemic, and Multi-Omics Analysis
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R: person("Peekei", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "you@example.com")
Description: A collection of high-level analytical pipelines wrapping common
    workflows in biostatistics and bioinformatics. Includes Cox proportional
    hazards survival analysis with a full diagnostic suite:
    unadjusted-versus-adjusted comparison, global and covariate-level
    proportional hazards testing, influence diagnostics (dfbeta/dfbetas),
    functional form checks via martingale residuals, and a written assumption
    verification verdict, in the style of a methods section rather than a
    single point estimate. Also includes a Bayesian hierarchical negative
    binomial mixed model pipeline for longitudinal RNA-seq count data, with
    gene-level partial pooling of the effect of interest, convergence
    diagnostics, posterior predictive checks, and a shrinkage plot. Also
    includes stochastic SIR/SEIR epidemic simulation via Gillespie's direct
    method, with an ensemble summary across realizations, final-size and
    peak-timing distributions, the implied basic reproduction number, and
    the probability of early stochastic extinction. Also includes multi-omics
    data integration via regularized generalized canonical correlation
    analysis, with per-block variance explained, a bootstrap-based loading
    stability check, and sample-score visualization across blocks.
